## Article 5 - Conventional year of first registration, provisions for changes of course or renunciation of studies

- 1. The requirements of merit, as referred to in article 8 and 9 of this Notice, that must be met by students always refer to the conventional year of first registration. The conventional year of first registration is considered to be:

- a) for students registered on first level bachelor degree courses and on single-cycle master's degree courses and on previous system degree courses, the academic year of first registration to University or AFAM institutions;
- b) for students registered on second level degree courses, the academic year of first registration for the second level degree to University or AFAM institutions.


- 2. The conventional year of first registration in the following cases is determined as follows:


- a) for University or AFAM students for whom it has been established “the change in course without validation of previous career”, the conventional year of registration is the first year of enrolment to the previous career;
- b) for students who, after having attended a bachelor degree (with or without graduation) are admitted or have been admitted to a single-cycle master's degree, in the presence of


- validation by the University of credits previously obtained, are counted all years of enrollment from the conventional year of first enrollment in the bachelor's degree, including 2025/2026, and any years of non-enrollment between courses (bachelor's and single-cycle master's degrees);
- c) for students to whom credits achieved in previous careers (Italian and/or abroad) are recognized and validated, even after the submission of the application for benefits, the conventional year of enrolment is the first year of enrolment in the previous career;
- d) for students who obtain exemptions from educational obligations through the validation of credits (previously obtained) not delivered in Italian or foreign university courses, the conventional year of registration is the first year of enrolment at the University of Genoa. In order to assess whether or not the requirement of merit is met, only credits acquired from the University of Genoa will be considered.
- e) for students who make the transfer / leave from another Italian University or AFAM Institution, it will be considered as conventional year the one of first enrolment at the course of origin. In order to be admitted to the competition for ALiSEO benefits, students must be validly registered with the University of Genoa by 31 December 2025;
- f) for students who obtain exemptions from educational obligations through the validation of credits previously obtained during international mobility programmes, the conventional year of registration is the first year of enrolment at the University of Genoa. In order to assess whether or not the requirement of merit is met, only credits acquired form the University of Genoa will be considered.
- g) for students who have renounced their studies in connection with their “previous career”, enrolling ex novo to a course for the first time, the years of registration will not be counted and neither will changes of course prior to academic year 2025/2026;
- h) for students who have obtained from University, pursuant to art. 9, paragraph 4 and 5 of Legislative Decree no. 68 of 29 March 2012, the granting of the exemption from the payment of the fees for the interruption of the studies, the years for which the University ordered the exemption are not counted;
- i) for students who obtain exemption from educational obligations through the recognition of credits obtained in the year of enrolment in “individual courses”, the conventional year of first enrolment is the first year of the course for which the benefits are requested. For the purposes of evaluating the merit requirement for obtaining benefits, credits acquired in the year of enrolment in “individual courses” are not considered.


3. Students who are enrolled for the academic year 2023/2024 cannot apply for benefits for a course year if they have already applied for benefits for the same year to ALiSEO or to another Italian Institutions for right to University study, even in case of a change of course “with” or “without” exam validation and/or renunciation of studies. Please note that the aforementioned provision does not apply to students who:

a) have not completed their enrolment at the University or at AFAM Institutions for the same course year for which they intend to re-apply for benefits; b) have been “excluded” from the final ALiSEO rankings for the same course year for which they intend to re-apply for benefits.

4. On the basis of the M.I.U.R and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Interior provisions on the matter of access for foreign students to university courses, for the purpose of issuing an entry visa for Italian territory for reasons of study, non-EU students who make study renunciation must return

to their country of origin and, in order to enrol in another course at the University, they must request a new entry visa for reasons of study.

## Article 12 – Supplements to the scholarship

1. The amounts of the scholarship as per article 17 (Table no. 8) of the present Notice may be supplemented, only in the following cases for the students:

- a) with disability as per article 13 of this Notice, equal to 25% of the gross amount of the scholarship.
- b) students admitted by the University and AFAM Institutions to take part in international mobility programs (EU and non-EU) for the academic year 2025/2026, as determined by Article 14 of this Notice;
- c) students achieving the degree within the duration envisaged by the respective course outlines with a final note comprehended between 99 and 110 (degree award).


These students will have to submit a request of “Integration of the scholarship for graduated students”, exclusively through the online procedure, by logging on to www.aliseo.liguria.it.student webdesk in the terms indicated on the institutional website of ALiSEO (under the section University Economic Benefits), within 30 days from the degree session in order to benefit from a supplement to the scholarship equal to half the monetary amount (net of supplements) obtained in the last year of the course. This supplement does not apply to students who have obtained a degree on old university degree courses activated prior to the implementation of Ministerial Decree 509/1999 and doctorate and specialisation school courses. The “degree award” is granted only in case of granting the scholarship to all students for a.y. 2025/2026.

It is specified that students may apply for the degree award if they obtain their degree within the term envisaged by their respective teaching regulations with reference to the academic year 2024/2025 and have applied for benefits for the academic year 2025/2026 as:

- • ‘last semester’ or ‘seventh semester + first year of master's degree’ and are enrolled in the first year out of course for the a.y. 2025/2026;
- • ‘seventh semester + first year of a master's degree’ and are enrolled in a first year of a master's degree for the academic year 2025/2026;
- • ‘last semester’ and are enrolled in a first year of a Master's degree for the academic year 2025/2026;
- • ‘last semester’ and are not enrolled for the academic year 2025/2026.


d) with an ISEEU/ISEEUP less than or equal to 50% (€ 13.974,00) of the maximum reference limit (€ 27.948,00) equal to 15% of the gross amount of the scholarship; e) with enrolment in courses of study in S.T.E.M subjects (defined by the MUR) with reference to female students only, equal to 15% of the gross amount of the scholarship;

f) enrolled simultaneously in more than one course of study, equal to 20% of the gross amount of the scholarship. The integration is not due in the event that the student loses the requirements for the grant with reference to the course of study to which the student has linked the said increment. The request for the supplement referred to in this letter must be submitted from 1 October 2025 to 15 October 2025 at 12.00 p.m. through the online procedure.

- 2. It should be specified, with reference to the integrations referred to in subparagraphs d) e) and f), as follows:

- a) the integrations referred to in letter d) and e) are not cumulative. Therefore, in the event that the student meets both the conditions, only the integration of paragraph e) is disbursed;
- b) the integrations referred to in letters d), e) and f) are disbursed in the methods provided for the disbursement of the scholarship with reference to the student's enrolment, with the exception of the student enrolled in subsequent years of Bachelor's degree and Master's degree, to whom the integration referred to in letter f) is disbursed at the same time as the second instalment of the scholarship;
- c) with reference to simultaneous enrolment in several courses of study referred to in letter f), the scholarship and the related services may be obtained exclusively for only one enrolment primarily specified in the application for benefits.


- 3. The integrations referred to in this Article shall be disbursed at 50% for students enrolled for the academic year 2025/2026 in a “last semester”.

## Article 13 - Scholarship Integration and Benefits Facilitation for Students with Disabilities (recognition of disability pursuant to Article 3 paragraph 1 of Law No. 104 of February 5, 1992, or with disability of 66% or more)

- 1. For the purpose of applying for the scholarship integration referred to in this article, students with recognition of disability pursuant to Article 3 paragraph 1 of Law No. 104 of February 5, 1992, or with disability equal to or greater than 66% are considered as disabled, pursuant to Decree of the Ministry of University and Research No. 1320 of December 17, 2021. These students, in order to be eligible for the benefits listed in Paragraph 2 below, when submitting the application to ALiSEO, must check the box “Integration of students with disabilities (art. 3 paragraph 1 law no. 104/92) or with disabilities of 66% or more” (Integrazione studenti con riconoscimento handicap (art. 3 comma 1 legge n. 104/92) o con invalidità pari o superiore al 66%”).
- 2. These students profit from the following benefits, some of which have already been mentioned in the previous articles referred to in this Notice:


a. the supplement of 25% of the net amount of the scholarship; b. the granting of the benefits, limited to the first title for each level of study, is guaranteed for a period of time, calculated from the conventional year of first registration, increased by additional semesters compared to non-disabled students, as reported in the previous article 3.3 of this Notice;

c. the priority of allocation in the rankings for scholarship and accommodation compared to non-disabled students; d. a facilitated merit-based requirement for students enrolled in years subsequent to the first (see Table nr. 4);

- e. the payment of the scholarship, including the integration for disabled students, in a single payment, by 31 December 2025, for students enrolled in the first years of all courses without the merit-based requirement referred to in the previous article 8 paragraph 6 of this Notice;
- f. two daily free meals at ALiSEO Canteen Service Centres;


- g. the right for the student assignee of accommodation to choose between the allocation of the accommodation and the money integration to the scholarship, equal to the amount of the Accomodation Service as per Table n. 8, if considered more suitable to the student needs (see art. 22)
- h. disbursement of the Accomodation Service portion referred to in Table No. 8 for the student eligible for accommodation and attending courses at the University or AFAM Institutions at locations where there is no availability of ALiSEO accommodations.


3. Students, in order to benefit from the integration referred to in this article, when submitting the application for benefits, must upload a valid certification attesting the recognition of disability in accordance with Article 3 Paragraph 1 of Law No. 104 of 5 February 1992, or disability of 66% or more, issued by the competent Italian Public Institution. If the student did not upload the above certification, ALiSEO will revoke the integration referred to in this article. Following the revocation of the above integration, ALISEO will also revoke the benefits if the student is in the following conditions:

a) student enrolled in years subsequent to the first who does not meet the merit-based requirements provided for non-disabled students as per Table n. 3; b) student enrolled in the first years of all courses who does not meet the merit-based requirement provided in the previous article 8, paragraph 2 of this Notice.

4. The amount related to the supplement for disabled students enrolled in years subsequent to the first one is paid in two instalments according to the deadlines of the scholarship payment.

## Article 16 - Criteria for the formulation of scholarship ranking lists

1. For students enrolled at the University, six rankings are prepared in accordance respectively to: a. students enrolled for the first year of a bachelor degree who are members of the European Union, in increasing order of University ISEEU/ISEEUP; b. students enrolled for the first year of a bachelor degree who are not members of the European Union, in increasing order of University ISEEU/ISEEUP; c. students enrolled for the first year of a second level specialised/master's degree who are members of the European Union, in increasing order of University ISEEU/ISEEUP;

- d. students enrolled for the first year of a second level specialised/master's degree who are not members of the European Union, in increasing order of Under the terms of University ISEEU/ISEEUP;
- e. students enrolled for years after the first of all courses of the current system: scholarships will be assigned according to the rankings of merit, according to the number of credits at 10 August 2025 in respect of credits or years required according to the conventional year of registration, as indicated under Article 9;
- f. students enrolled for the “seventh semester + first year of master's degree” as indicated under Article 9 of this notice, according to the number of credits at 10 August 2025, in respect of credits required according to the year of registration, as indicated under Article 9;


In case of equal situations: a) in the first four rankings (letters a), b), c), d), the youngest in terms of age shall precede; b) in the fifth and sixth rankings (letters e), f), the following priority criteria are applied:

 the student who does not benefit from the bonus;  the student who benefits from the bonus to a lesser extent;  the student who has the highest average marks;  the student who has been awarded an ALiSEO scholarship for academic year 2024/2025;  the student with the lowest ISEEU/ISEEUP.

2. For students enrolled at AFAM Institutions, rankings for each AFAM Institution will be prepared ranked as detailed below:

- a. students enrolled at the first year of a level 1 or 2 course who are members of the European Union: the ranking will be listed in increasing order of University ISEEU/ISEEUP;
- b. students enrolled at the first year of a level 1 or 2 course who are not members of the European Union: the ranking will be listed in increasing order of University ISEEU/ISEEUP;
- c. students enrolled at the subsequent years after the first, the scholarships will be assigned with rankings of merit drawn up according to the number of credits achieved as at 10 August 2025 , in respect of the minimum credits required by this competition Notice.


In case of equal situations: a) in the first two rankings (letters a), b), the youngest in terms of age shall precede; b) in the third ranking (letter c), the following priority criteria are applied:

 the student with the highest average marks;  the student with the lowest ISEEU/ISEEUP.

- 3. For students enrolled at specialisation courses or PhD courses, a ranking is drawn up in order of increasing ISEE/ISEEUP, in which students enrolled at years after the first precede.
- 4. In situations in which the economic position is equal, the student awarded with an ALiSEO scholarship for the academic year 2024/2025 shall precede.

