### 17.2 Payment of the scholarship and provision of the services

- 1. Students enrolled in years subsequent to the first awarded in the final ranking list of the scholarships are entitled:

- a) to the payment of the amount of the scholarship according to the provisions and modalities provided for in Article 24 of this Notice;
- b) to take advantage daily of a first meal free of charge and a second meal at the “scholarship winner rate” (see Canteen Service Provisions), at the ALiSEO Canteen Service Centres, during the opening periods starting from the day after the publication of the final a.y. 2025/2026 rankings and until the publication of the final a.y. 2026/2027 rankings;
- c) to take advantage of the free accommodation place or the rental contribution as per art. 22 of the present Application Requirements and Regulations, if they are “off-site students”and eligible assignees of the accommodation place, in ALiSEO's housing facilities.
- d) to benefit from free accommodation in ALiSEO's housing facilities, if they are “off-site students”and assignees. For the modalities and dates for the assignment of accommodation, refer to articles 19 and 20 of this Notice.


- 2. Students resulted as “last semester” winners of the scholarship in the definitive ranking for are entitled:

- a) to the payment of 50% of the amount of the scholarship indicated in Table n. 8 in accordance with the provisions and modalities set in the previous article 9.4 of this Notice;
- b) to daily benefit from a first free meal and a second meal at the “scholarship winner rate” (see Canteen Service Provisions) at the ALiSEO Canteen Service Centres, during the opening periods from the day after the publication of the final a.y. 2025/2026 rankings until graduation or, in any case, until 31 March 2026;
- c) to take advantage of the free accommodation place or the rental contribution referred to in Article 22 of this Notice of Competition, if they are off-site students eligible for accommodation, until they graduate or in any case until 31 March 2026. It should be noted that starting from 1 April 2026 the student awarded a six-month scholarship is required to pay for meals according to the “bracket tariff” (see Provisions for Canteen Service) and for the monthly rent of € 200.00 until graduation;
- d) the deadline of 31 March 2026 is to be considered valid unless the University extends the deadline for the last session of final exams for the graduation for the academic year 2024/2025.


- 3. Students enrolled in the first years of all degree courses awarded in the final ranking of scholarships are entitled:


- a) to the payment of the amount of the scholarship in accordance with the provisions and modalities set in the Article 8 of this Notice.
- b) to daily benefit of a first meal free of charge and a second meal at the “scholarship winner rate” (see Canteen Service Provisions), at the ALiSEO Canteen Service Centres, during the


opening periods starting from the day after the publication of the final a.y. 2025/2026 rankings and until the publication of the final a.y. 2026/2027 rankings;

c) to benefit of the free accommodation place or of the rental contribution referred toin Article 22 of this notice, if they are off-site students eligible for accommodation, until the deadline provided for in Article 20.3 of this notice.

4. Students awarded in the final ranking of scholarships as “Seventh semester + first year of a master's degree” are entitled:

- a) to the payment of the amount of the scholarship according to the provisions and modalities provided for in Article 9.3 of this Notice;
- b) to daily benefit from a first free meal and a second meal at the “scholarship winner rate” (Canteen Service Regulation) at the ALiSEO Catering Centres, during the opening periods starting from the day after the publication of the final a.y. 2025/2026 rankings and until the publication of the final a.y. 2026/2027 rankings and until:


- - 31 March 2026, for students enrolled in the last semester;
- - the publication of the definitive rankings for the 2026/2027 academic year, for students enrolled at the first year of a Master's degree;


c) to benefit of the free accommodation place or of the rental contribution referred toin Article 22 of this notice, if they are off-site students eligible for accommodation, until:

- - graduation from a bachelor degree course or, in any case, no later than 31 March 2026 for students enrolled in their final semester;
- - the deadline established in the article 20.3 of this notice for students enrolled in a first year of a Master's degree.


- 5. Students enrolled in PhD courses and specialisation schools awarded in the final ranking of scholarships are entitled to:

- a) the payment of the amount of the scholarship according to the provisions and modalities provided for in Article 24.3 of this Notice;
- b) daily benefit from a first free meal and a second meal at the “scholarship winner rate” (Canteen Service Regulation) at the ALiSEO Canteen Service Centres, during the opening periods starting from the day after the publication of the final a.y. 2025/2026 rankings and until the publication of the final a.y. 2026/2027 rankings;
- c) to benefit of the free accommodation place or of the rental contribution referred toin Article 22 of this notice, if they are off-site students eligible for accommodation, until the deadline provided for in Article 20.3 of this notice.


- 6. In the case of withdrawal of benefits, the "Commuting" or "Off-site" student (if assignee) must reimburse the costs of any services used (accommodation and catering).

### 19.3 New requests of subsequent years

1. The places made available after the assignments pursuant to 19.2 paragraph, will be assigned to students not housed in residences in academic year 2024/2025 enrolled in years subsequent to the first year of all courses (new requests). Rankings will be ordered according to decreasing points obtained from the following formula:

student credits - min. credits 1000 X --------------------------------------max. credits - min. credits

- - Credits : means the number of credits acquired by 10/08/2025;
- - Min. credits: means the number of credits corresponding to the minimum requirement of merit for access to benefits in connection with the year of registration (tab. 3, 4);
- - Max. credits: means the maximum number of credit potentially able to be sustained by the student until the year of course prior to that relating to the registration in 2025/2026.


2. In the event of parity, the following priority criteria will be considered:  the student who has not used the bonus credits;

 the student who has made least use of the bonus credits;  the student with the lowest ISEEU/ISEEUP.

