## Article 22 - Rental contribution

- 1. Students awarded scholarships who are not accomodated due to lack of places or students eligible but attending courses at the University or AFAM Institutions at sites where there is no ALiSEO housing available, will be granted a scholarship increased by the amount corresponding to the value attributed to the accommodation service (Table 8) related to the period of unavailability of accommodation place calculated over 10 months. The aforementioned contract must be duly registered with the Italian Internal Revenue Service and/ or any renewal with the successful registration with the Italian Internal Revenue Service, in accordance with Law No. 431 of December 9, 1998, “Discipline of leases and release of real estate for residential use” as amended and supplemented; A exception to the duly registered contract is permitted in the case of a contract for a rooming house or Residence/College, not subject to registration, which, however, must contain the clauses governing hospitality and the signature of the parties.
- 2. students who renounce the accommodation are also ineligible to apply for the rental contribution referred to in this article;
- 3. Students eligible for accommodation as a result of subsequent sliding of the final rankings have a choice between accommodation assignment and the rental contribution;
- 4. Students referred to in Paragraph 3 above who opt for the allocation of accommodation by completing the entrance procedures, and subsequently renounce the accommodation place, will not be refunded security deposit, but will maintain the status of " off-site”.

