### 24.2 Students enrolled at first years

1. The scholarship is paid/awarded, in the amount due, as follows: a) for students enrolled at the first year of a bachelor degree or a single-cycle master’s degree:

 20% of the total amount of the scholarship by 10 November 2025;  30% of the total amount of the scholarship by 31 December 2025;  50% of the total amount of the scholarship upon achievement of 20 CFU by 10 August

2026;

b) for students enrolled at the year of a master's degree:  50% of the total amount of the scholarship by 31 December 2025;  50% of the total amount of the scholarship upon achievement of 20 CFU by 10 August

2026;

- 2. The payment of the 20% and 30% amounts mentioned in letter a) and the 50% amount of the first instalment mentioned in letter b) of the preceding paragraph is constituted in priority for “Commuting” and “Off-site” students, by the share in services of the scholarship (one free meal at the ALiSEO Canteen centres and free accommodation for the academic year 2025/2026). If the portion disbursed in services is not sufficient to cover the value of 50% of the scolarship, ALiSEO will provide the remaining monetary difference.
- 3. For students registered for degree courses in medical professions, run by the School of Medical and Pharmaceutical Sciences, who complete the technical-practical traineeships scheduled for the 2025/2026 academic year, the relevant credits will be counted if achieved and recorded by 31 October 2026 by the University on the student’s exam self-certification (“Autocertificazione esami”);
- 4. Disabled students, as per article 13 of this Notice, enrolled at the first year of all study courses, will receive the amount of the scholarship as a lump sum, without respecting the merit requirement (20 CFU by 10/8/2026) by:


a) November 10, 2025 for the first years of bachelor's degree and single-cycle master's degree; b) December 31, 2025 for the first years of master's degree.

### 25.1 Grounds for non-admission
The following cases represent grounds for non-admission:

a) failure to comply with the deadlines for the application for benefits of which at Article 7 of the present Notice;

- b) failure to submit the application (even in case of partial or complete compiling of the said application);
- c) the application for benefits for students enrolled, in the academic year 2025/2026, with the first year of a first level degree or a single-cycle master’s degree who are age 35 or older before the cut off date for application;;
- d) application for accommodation for students registered, in the academic year 2025/2026 who have not reached the age of 18 at the deadline for application; e) students excluded from benefits competitions in previous years for having made untruthful declarations with the application of the administrative sanction;


f) to students who owe money to AliSEO, ARTE (Azienda Regionale Territoriale per l’Edilizia) or other Entities for the Right to University Study, unless repayment plans have been agreed and that they are regularly respected;

### 25.2 Grounds for exclusion or revocation of benefits

1. The following cases represent grounds for exclusion or revocation of benefits: a) students with a conventional first year registration exceeding the number of semesters for which the benefit can be granted; b) students (with the exception of students who have applied for the academic year 2025/2026 as the first year of a master's degree), who have not completed registration for academic year 2025/2026 by 31/12/2025; c) students who, by submitting an application for benefits such as “seventh semester + 1st year of a master's degree”, have not completed enrolment at seventh semester by 31 December 2025 or for a first year of a master's degree by 10 March 2026 at the University for the academic year 2025/2026; d) students applying for benefits as first year of a master’s degree who have not completed registration at University for the academic year 2025/2026, by 10 March 2026 (or by the deadline otherwise indicated by the University departments for graduation); e) students who have applied as ‘seventh semester + first year of a master's degree’ or ‘first year of a master's degree’ and are enrolled for the academic year 2025/2026 in learning activities aimed at enrolling in a master's degree (‘bridge career’) or ‘ single courses’ after 10/3/2026; f) AFAM students who have not completed their enrollment for the 2025/2026 academic year by the dates provided by the respective AFAM institutions; g) students who have applied for ALiSEO benefits for the academic year 2025/2026 as enrolled in:

- • “first year” and are enrolled at a “subsequent year”;
- • “subsequent year” and are enrolled at a “first year”


- h) students who are enrolled at a subsequent year in a different year than the self-certified one at the time of submitting the benefit application and therefore result as not in possession of the minimum merit requirement;
- i) students who have applied for benefits for the academic year 2025/2026 as ‘last semester’ or ‘seventh semester + first year of a Master's degree’ and are enrolled for the academic year 2025/2026 in a last semester and obtain a degree in progress with reference to the academic year 2024/2025 (current graduates);
- j) students who enrol at the University or AFAM Institutions for the academic year 2024/2025 to obtain a degree of equal level or lower than the one already acquired, in particular:


- • students in possession of a degree from the previous system who enrol at a bachelor degree course, single-cycle master's degree, second-level master's degree, a first or second level diploma from the AFAM institutions;
- • students with a university diploma who enrol at a bachelor degree course;
- • students in possession of a bachelor degree or single-cycle master's degree who enrol at another bachelor degree course or single-cycle master's degree, or who are in possession of a second-level master's degree who enrol at a second-cycle or single-cycle master's degree course;
- • students with a specialisation or PhD degree who enrol at another PhD course or specialisation school;


- • students with a bachelor degree or a first-level diploma from an AFAM Institution who enrol at a bachelor degree course or a AFAM first-level diploma course;
- • students with a master's degree or second level diploma from an AFAM institution who enrol


at a second-level degree course or a second-level AFAM diploma course; k) students who have obtained a degree from an Italian or foreign University recognised in Italy (equivalence of the degree) of the same level as that for which they require the benefits for the academic year 2025/2026; l) students who transfer from other universities or AFAM Institutions (Italian or foreign) and are not enrolled by 31/12/2025 or by 10/3/2026 for students who have applied for benefits as first-year master degree students;

- m) students whose enrolment is cancelled or who obtain a transfer/leave to other Universities or other AFAM Institutions (Italian or foreign) by 31/12/2025. It should be noted that cancellation due to a leave for academic year 2025/2026 may be ordered by the University on enrolment for academic year 2026/2027;
- n) students enrolled for more semesters than the number of semesters required by this Notice considering, in case of validation of exams from a previous course and/or career (Italian or foreign), as year conventional of first enrollment the one made in the previous course and/or career at the University Genoa or other Italian or foreign University;
- o) students who are enrolled for the academic year 2025/2026, in a course year for which they have already applied for the benefits to ALiSEO or to another Italian Right to University Study Institution also following a change of course "with exam validation" or "without exam validation” or withdrawal from studies; p) students who withdraw from their studies after the publication of the final rankings; q) students who withdraw their granted benefits, including any supplements; r) students who lose the minimum merit requirements for the 2025/2026 academic year as a result of the final enrolment change and/or "validation of examinations" from a previous career; s) students not meeting the merit and/or income requirements following an examination by ALiSEO; t) students who, when notified by the Financial Benefits Service for verifications, do not present themselves by the date foreseen in the convocation notice, sent to the email address indicated by the student in the application for benefits, or do not present the required documentation on time; u) students not meeting the requirements to apply for the scholarship supplements referred to in art. 12 of theof this notice. These students will have their supplementary benefit withdrawn, subject to verification of the maintenance of the other benefits (scholarship and accommodation); v) students with disabilities referred to in article 13 of this notice who, following the withdrawal of the scholarship in the aforementioned article, do not meet the merit requirements envisaged for non-disabled students; w) students enrolled in the first year of all courses in the 2025/2026 academic year who have not obtained at least 20 credits by 30 November 2026; x) students benefiting from other monetary benefits, relating to the same academic year, for any title awarded by public or private bodies (including the University), including scholarships issued to foreign students by the Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, having the same purpose as he scholarship or that have been explicitly declared incompatible with the scholarship itself. ease note that the student may opt for the enjoyment of either benefit. An exception to the above is made for:


- • scholarships granted by national and foreign institutions to supplement with stays abroad the training or research activities of scholarship holders and for part-time collaboration or tutoring assignments granted by the University;
- • benefits granted by other institutions for the sole purpose of meeting the costs for the housing service costs. In this case, "off-site" students will not be able to benefit from the housing service and/or subsidy rent and will be considered "commuters".


y) students who, as a result of the withdrawal of their grant, lose the right to obtain the supplements referred to in article 12 of this notice;

z) students who are in debt to ALiSEO, or to other organisations for the Right to University Study; aa) in the cases provided for in the Provisions on Student Residences; bb) in the cases provided for in the Provisions for the Catering Service; cc) students to whom, in the event of passage with or without validation of examinations, dismissal from a course and/or a previous career (Italian or foreign), is verified to have a different conventional year of first enrolment than the one declared when the application for the benefits was submitted; dd) students enrolled in part-time courses; ee) students enrolled in master's degrees courses; ff) students who have already applied for benefits from ALiSEO, or from another Italian Right to University Study Institution, for the same course year for which they have applied for the a.y. 2025/2026; gg) students who, following verifications, are found to be indebted to ALiSEO or other Italian Right to University Studies Institutions for academic years prior to 2025/2026, unless repayment plans have been agreed and the same are duly complied with; hh) students who, despite being beneficiaries in the definitive rankings, have not obtained the Visa necessary for entry into Italy; ii) students who have applied as first-year bachelor degree or single-cycle master's degree and are enrolled for the 2025/2026 academic year in ‘individual courses’ after 31/12/2025; jj) students who are not in possession of the ISEEUP certificate by 31/12/2025.

- 2. The Economic Benefits Service reserves the right to assess any further causes of exclusion not covered in the above-mentioned points that may be in the nature of an impediment to the maintenance of the requested benefits.
- 3. Whenever ALiSEO ascertains the existence of such conditions of non-admission or exclusion during verifications following the publication of the final rankings, the benefits are revoked.
- 4. An appeal against the revocation decision may be submitted to the T.A.R. Liguria (Administrative Court of the Region of Liguria) within 60 days from the notification of the revocation or submit an extraordinary appeal to the President of the Italian Republic within 120 days from its publication.
- 5. Students who forfeit their benefits must reimburse the scholarship (including integrations) and any services enjoyed as a “scholarship” student (at ‘'bracket’ or 'out of bracket" rates depending on the reason for the revocation for the canteen service and at the rates indicated in Table no. 10 for the accommodation service), unless the forfeiture is due to untruthful declarations: in this case, the provisions of article 26, paragraph 4 of this Notice of Competition apply. 6. Students who lose their eligibility for benefits between the publication of the provisional rankings ( scholarships and accommodation) and the final rankings ( scholarships and accommodation) must reimburse any services enjoyed (accommodation and/or canteen) during this period.


7. The act of revocation is notified to the University and to the AFAM Institutions, which, in accordance with the current regulations, order the revocation of the related contribution benefits. Therefore, any modification to the student's career occurred after the revocation of benefits, already ordered by administrative act against the students, will not be taken into consideration for the purposes of reviewing eligibility for benefits.

